.TH man_1_simple_shell

.Dd April 09, 2019

.Os [OS] [seashell/v1]

.SH NAME man_1_simple_shell Project


.Sh SYNOPSIS

.Nd /bin/ls [-l][-la][-a] Displays a list of files in stdout in varied formats

.Nd /bin/pwd Displays a directory path to stdout

.Nd pwd Displays a directory path after implementation of stat


.Sh DESCRIPTION

Simple_shell prints the commands to stdout and is able to support basic shell commands and their functionality. To activate our simple_shell, user has to compile the program and run a ./a.out command to enter the simple shell.

.Sh Examples of common usage

- pwd lists the directory paths in this format /home/vagrant/holbertonschool-low_level_programming/simple_shell

- ls will list the files in the current directory in this format

README.md  a.out  seashell.h  super_simple_shell.c


.Sh Command [Options]

.Sh ls [options]

.Op -a Ar - list all files including hidden file starting with

.Op –color Ar - colored list [=always/never/auto]

.Op -d Ar - list directories - with ' */'

.Op -F Ar - add one char of */=>@| to enteries

.Op -i Ar - list file's inode index number

.Op -l Ar - list with long format - show permissions

.Op -la Ar - list long format including hidden files

.Op -lh Ar - list long format with readable file size

.Op -ls Ar - list with long format with file size

.Op -r Ar - list in reverse order

.Op -R Ar - list recursively directory tree

.Op -s Ar - list file size

.Op -S sort by file size

.Op -t Ar - sort by time & date

.Op -X Ar - sort by extension name


.Sh pwd [option]

.Op cd Ar changes working directory

.Op pwd Ar print working directory

.Sh Other options

.Op exit Ar exits the shell

.Op Ctrl + D Ar exits the shell

.Sh FILES

- simple_shell
- man_1_simple_shell
- AUTHORS


.Sh ENVIRONMENT


**DEFAULT ‘$’ prompt **

The default dedication if none is given. Has the highest precedence
    if a no command is supplied on the command line the $ will wait until exited using Ctrl + D or exit is typed.

